[[File:Equity, diversity, inclusion (30275120034).jpg|thumb|Flyer supporting equity, diversity, and inclusion in 2016]]
'''Diversity, equity, and inclusion''' ('''DEI''') are organizational frameworks which seek to promote the fair treatment and full participation of all people, particularly groups who have historically been underrepresented or subject to [[discrimination]] on the basis of [[identity (social science)|identity]] or [[disability]].<ref>{{Cite web |title='DEI' – on Dictionary.com |url=https://www.dictionary.com/browse/dei |access-date=2023-03-25 |website=dictionary.com |language=en}}</ref> These three notions ([[diversity (politics)|diversity]], [[social equity|equity]], and [[social exclusion#Social inclusion|inclusion]]) together represent "three closely linked values" which organizations seek to institutionalize through DEI frameworks.<ref name="mckinsey">{{cite web |title=What is diversity, equity, and inclusion? |url=https://www.mckinsey.com/featured-insights/mckinsey-explainers/what-is-diversity-equity-and-inclusion |publisher=McKinsey & Company |access-date=25 March 2023 |date=17 August 2022}}</ref> The concepts predate this terminology and other variations sometimes include terms such as '''belonging''', '''justice''', and '''accessibility'''. As such, frameworks such as '''inclusion and diversity''' ('''I&D'''),<ref>{{cite web |title=What is Inclusion & Diversity? |url=https://www.iilondon.co.uk/home/about-us/inclusion-diversity/what-is-inclusion-diversity |access-date=18 July 2024 |website=The Insurance Institute of London}}</ref> '''diversity, equity, inclusion and belonging''' ('''DEIB'''),<ref name="cut">{{cite news |last1=Read |first1=Bridget |title=Inside the Booming Diversity-Equity-and-Inclusion Industrial Complex |url=https://www.thecut.com/article/diversity-equity-inclusion-industrial-companies.html |access-date=21 September 2022 |work=The Cut |date=26 May 2021 |language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Diversity, Equity, Inclusion and Belonging (DEIB) |url=https://www.bi.edu/about-bi/deib/ |website=bi.edu |publisher=[[BI Norwegian Business School]] |access-date=25 March 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=The Office of Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Belonging |url=https://diversity.ku.edu/about |publisher=University of Kansas |access-date=25 March 2023}}</ref> '''justice, equity, diversity and inclusion''' ('''JEDI''' or '''EDIJ'''),<ref>{{cite news |last1=Hammond |first1=J. W. |last2=Brownell |first2=Sara E. |last3=Kedharnath |first3=Nita A. |last4=Cheng |first4=Susan J. |last5=Byrd |first5=W. Carson |title=Why the Term 'JEDI' Is Problematic for Describing Programs That Promote Justice, Equity, Diversity and Inclusion |url=https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/why-the-term-jedi-is-problematic-for-describing-programs-that-promote-justice-equity-diversity-and-inclusion/ |access-date=25 March 2023 |publisher=Scientific American |date=23 September 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Office of Equity, Diversity, Inclusion, and Justice (EDIJ) |url=https://lesley.edu/department-search/office-of-diversity-equity-and-inclusion-dei |website=Lesley University |access-date=25 March 2023}}</ref> or '''diversity, equity, inclusion and accessibility''' ('''IDEA''', '''DEIA''' or '''DEAI''')<ref>{{cite web |title=Inclusion, Diversity, Equity, and Access (IDEA) |date=30 April 2018 |url=https://www.aam-us.org/programs/diversity-equity-accessibility-and-inclusion/facing-change-definitions/ |publisher=Indiana Arts Commission |access-date=25 March 2023}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Definitions of Diversity, Equity, Accessibility, and Inclusion |url=https://www.aam-us.org/programs/diversity-equity-accessibility-and-inclusion/facing-change-definitions/ |access-date=25 March 2023 |publisher=American Alliance of Museums}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Executive Order on Diversity, Equity, Inclusion, and Accessibility in the Federal Workforce |url=https://www.whitehouse.gov/briefing-room/presidential-actions/2021/06/25/executive-order-on-diversity-equity-inclusion-and-accessibility-in-the-federal-workforce/ |access-date=25 March 2023 |publisher=whitehouse.gov |date=25 June 2021}}</ref> exist.

''Diversity'' refers to the presence of variety within the organizational workforce, such as in [[identity (social science)|identity]] and [[identity politics]]. It includes [[gender identity|gender]], [[ethnicity]], [[sexual orientation]], [[disability]], [[aging|age]], [[cultural diversity|culture]], [[social class|class]], [[religious identity|religion]], or [[opinion]].<ref name="mckinsey"/><ref name="abcnews">{{cite news |last1=Alfonseca |first1=Kiara |title=DEI: What does it mean and what is its purpose? |url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/dei-programs/story?id=97004455 |access-date=25 March 2023 |publisher=ABC News |date=10 Februar
